    <who name="Guy Taylor">thebigguy.co.uk</who>
    <bug_when>2017-02-19 17:20:26 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>As it is common for archive packages to be compressed with bzip2 (tar.bz2) the flatpak-builder RPM package should depend on bzip2. This would help prevent painful debugging of build errors and make it &quot;Just Work&quot;â„¢ in more situations.

Example affected build spec: https://github.com/KDE/flatpak-kde-applications/blob/c7b34f2d19cf4a951fda7d1900094ccfdff050b8/org.kde.krita.json#L32</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
    <commentid>10165051</commentid>
    <comment_count>1</comment_count>
      <attachid>1255554</attachid>
    <who name="Guy Taylor">thebigguy.co.uk</who>
    <bug_when>2017-02-19 17:34:15 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>Created attachment 1255554
Require bzip2 for flatpak-builder

I am new to RPMs coming from the DEB world but I believe this would solve the issue.

Note: flatpak-builder does not call &quot;bzip2&quot; itself bit uses &quot;tar -j&quot;.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
